This is the script of making figure 2 including: Comparesion of immune cell proportion traits

library(ggplot2)
library(ggpubr)
library(cowplot)

Comparison of immune cell proportion traits using all samples:

DM<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/comparison/DM5P_GPenPCalc_Percent_matchedRtHversion.txt",header=T,row.names=1,sep="\t",check.names = F)

phe_DM<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/comparison/phe_300DM.txt",header=T,row.names = 1)

ol<-intersect(rownames(DM),rownames(phe_DM))

DM<-DM[ol,]
phe_DM<-phe_DM[ol,]
DM<-DM[,1:149]

FG<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/comparison/ccount_cpercent_500FG.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t")
phe_FG<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/comparison/500FG_basic_phenotypes.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t")

ol<-intersect(rownames(FG),rownames(phe_FG))
FG<-FG[ol,]
phe_FG<-phe_FG[ol,]
FG<-FG[,92:ncol(FG)]

####
anno<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/comparison/list.txt",header=T,sep="\t",check.names = F)
rownames(anno)<-anno$`300DM`
anno<-anno[names(DM),]
names(DM)<-anno$`500FG`

Make figures of examples shown in manuscript

##T reg example
exam1<-data.frame(percent=c(FG$Treg_HLANDRP_PBMC_LMI4_grandparentPerc__Index78,DM$Treg_HLANDRP_PBMC_LMI4_grandparentPerc__Index78),group=c(rep("500FG",nrow(FG)),rep("300DM",nrow(DM))))
exam1$group<-factor(exam1$group,levels = c("500FG","300DM"))

p1 <- ggboxplot(data=exam1, x="group", y="percent", color="group", add="jitter", short.panel.labs=F,width = 0.5)+ylab("Activated Treg")
p1=p1 + stat_compare_means(comparisons= list(c("500FG","300DM")),label="p.format",method="t.test")+theme(legend.position = "none",axis.title.x = element_blank(),axis.text.x = element_blank())

#6,10

Sensitive analysis using a subset of samples with balenced ages.

keep_DM<-rownames(phe_DM)[which(phe_DM$Age>30 & phe_DM$Age<70)]
keep_FG<-rownames(phe_FG)[which(phe_FG$Age>30 & phe_FG$Age<70)]
t.test(phe_DM$Age[which(phe_DM$Age>30 & phe_DM$Age<70)],phe_FG$Age[which(phe_FG$Age>30 & phe_FG$Age<70)])

DM<-DM[keep_DM,]
FG<-FG[keep_FG,]

res<-rep(NA,ncol(DM))
res<-as.data.frame(res)
rownames(res)<-names(DM)
names(res)<-"pval"

for (i in names(DM)){
  t<-t.test(DM[,i],FG[,i])
  res[i,1]<-t$p.value
}

res<-transform(res,fdr=p.adjust(res$pval,method = "fdr"))

rownames(res)[which(res$fdr<0.05)]

anno_tmp<-anno
rownames(anno_tmp)<-anno$`500FG`
anno_tmp[rownames(res)[which(res$fdr<0.05)],]
